# Square corners on dense UI

For **admin routes**, **simulate**, **data tables**, and **full-width bordered sections** (form panels, event lists):

- Use **`rounded-none`** on bordered containers (`section`, table wrappers, panel-like blocks). Do not add `rounded-lg` / `rounded-md` to these surfaces unless the user explicitly asks.
- **Shadcn primitives** (`Button`, `Input`, `Dialog`) may keep default radii; the rule targets **layout shells** and **tables** where rounding reads as accidental styling.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — full-width insert panel
<section className="w-full rounded-none border border-border bg-card/30 p-4 sm:p-6">

// ❌ AVOID — unnecessary rounding on the same pattern
<section className="rounded-lg border ...">
```

When adding new bordered UI in `routes/admin/` or similar, default to **`rounded-none`** for the outer panel.
